          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Experimentally measured K0-factors and evaluated values",
                "for isotopic abundance and absolute gamma-intensities",
                "were used for determination 2200 m/sec cross-sections.",
                "Theoretical definition of K0 relative Au cross-section",
                "is K0=m(Au)*t*S0*g/(m*t(Au)*S0(Au)*g(Au)),where",
                "    m-atomic weight,t-isotopic abundance,S0- 2200 m/sec",
                "    (n,g) cross-section,g-absolute gamma-ray-intensity",
                "Experimental K0 value is",
                "K0=asp/asp(Au)*(F+q0(Au))/(F+q0)*Ep(Au)/Ep,where",
                "    asp-specific count rate,F-thermal (subcadmium) to",
                "    epithermal neutron flux ratio,q0-resonance integral",
                "    to 2200 m/sec cross-section ratio corrected for",
                "    non-ideal epithermal flux distribution,Ep-full",
                "    energy peak detection efficiency.(Au) means",
                "    respective value for Au-197 standard"
              ]
            }
          ],
